HEADWORD: Anura
<hw>A*nu"ra</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*n⟦umac⟧"r⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.
pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>'an</grk> priv. + <grk>o'yra`</grk> a
tail.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the orders of amphibians
characterized by the absence of a tail, as the frogs and toads.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>anoura</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

